('health_wellness', 'easy', 'What does BOAS stand for in relation to French Bulldog health?', 'Brachycephalic Obstructive Airway Syndrome', 'Breathing Obstruction and Airway Stenosis', 'Bulldog Obstructive Asthma Syndrome', 'Broad Airway Occlusion Syndrome', 'BOAS is caused by the flat-faced anatomy of brachycephalic breeds and can cause snoring, exercise intolerance, and breathing difficulty.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'Why can''t most French Bulldogs swim well?', 'Their heavy front body and short legs make them top-heavy', 'They are afraid of water', 'Their fur absorbs too much water', 'They have no webbing between their toes', 'Frenchies are top-heavy with a large head and chest relative to their hindquarters, making it very difficult to stay buoyant.', 'You should always put a life vest on a Frenchie near water.', 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'What is the average lifespan of a French Bulldog?', '10 to 12 years', '5 to 7 years', '15 to 18 years', '8 to 9 years', 'French Bulldogs typically live 10-12 years with proper care.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'Why are French Bulldogs at higher risk of heatstroke than most breeds?', 'Their flat faces make panting less efficient for cooling', 'They have thicker fur than most breeds', 'They drink less water', 'They produce more body heat', 'Dogs cool down by panting, which evaporates moisture from their airways. Brachycephalic breeds can''t pant as effectively.', 'Frenchies are twice as likely to suffer heatstroke compared to non-brachycephalic breeds.', 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'What common eye condition causes a red, swollen mass in the corner of a Frenchie''s eye?', 'Cherry eye', 'Glaucoma', 'Cataracts', 'Conjunctivitis', 'Cherry eye occurs when the gland of the third eyelid prolapses and becomes visible as a red, cherry-like mass.', 'Cherry eye usually requires surgery to reposition the prolapsed gland.', 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'What should you always use when a French Bulldog is near water?', 'A life vest', 'Water wings', 'A swimming instructor', 'Floaties', 'Due to their top-heavy build, Frenchies should always wear a canine life vest when near water.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'easy', 'Why do French Bulldogs snore so loudly?', 'Their flat faces and narrow airways restrict airflow', 'They sleep more deeply than other breeds', 'They have unusually large tongues', 'They dream more than other breeds', 'The shortened airways of brachycephalic breeds create turbulent airflow, resulting in characteristic loud snoring.', NULL, 0, 1),

('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What percentage of French Bulldog litters are delivered via C-section?', 'Over 80%', 'About 50%', 'About 30%', 'Less than 10%', 'Due to the puppies'' large heads relative to the mother''s narrow pelvis, the vast majority of Frenchie births require surgical intervention.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What spinal condition are French Bulldogs prone to due to their chondrodystrophic body type?', 'Intervertebral Disc Disease (IVDD)', 'Degenerative Myelopathy', 'Wobbler Syndrome', 'Spondylosis', 'IVDD causes discs between vertebrae to degenerate, bulge, and sometimes rupture, causing pain and potentially paralysis.', 'IVDD often strikes after age 2-3 in French Bulldogs.', 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What anatomical feature called "stenotic nares" is common in French Bulldogs?', 'Abnormally narrow nostrils', 'Oversized ear canals', 'Elongated soft palate only', 'Enlarged tonsils', 'Stenotic nares are pinched or narrow nostrils that restrict airflow. Surgery to widen them can greatly improve breathing.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What condition causes the kneecap to slip out of its normal groove in French Bulldogs?', 'Patellar luxation', 'ACL tear', 'Hip dysplasia', 'Osteochondritis dissecans', 'Patellar luxation is common in small breeds including Frenchies. You might see a Frenchie suddenly limp for a few steps then walk normally.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What vertebral condition involves malformed, wedge-shaped bones in the spine?', 'Hemivertebrae', 'Scoliosis', 'Spina bifida', 'Lordosis', 'Hemivertebrae are malformed vertebrae that can compress the spinal cord. They are relatively common in screw-tailed breeds like Frenchies.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What are the three main anatomical components of BOAS?', 'Elongated soft palate, stenotic nares, and narrow trachea', 'Large tongue, small lungs, and narrow ribcage', 'Short neck, flat face, and small nostrils only', 'Wide throat, small lungs, and narrow airways', 'BOAS involves an elongated soft palate, narrowed nostrils (stenotic nares), and a hypoplastic (undersized) trachea working together to obstruct airflow.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'Why are French Bulldogs more sensitive to anaesthesia than many other breeds?', 'Their compromised airways make breathing under sedation riskier', 'They metabolise drugs faster', 'They have smaller hearts', 'They are more allergic to medications', 'Brachycephalic breeds have higher anaesthesia risks due to their already compromised airways, requiring extra monitoring.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What skin condition is caused by moisture and bacteria trapped in French Bulldogs'' facial wrinkles?', 'Skin fold dermatitis', 'Mange', 'Ringworm', 'Eczema', 'The facial folds of Frenchies can trap moisture and bacteria, leading to irritation, yeast infections, and dermatitis if not kept clean and dry.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What type of allergies are French Bulldogs especially prone to?', 'Both food and environmental allergies', 'Only food allergies', 'Only seasonal allergies', 'Only contact allergies', 'Frenchies are prone to food allergies (especially beef, dairy, chicken) and environmental allergies (pollen, dust mites, mould).', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'Why should French Bulldogs avoid jumping on and off furniture?', 'It puts stress on their spine and increases IVDD risk', 'It damages their paw pads', 'It hurts their ears', 'It makes them dizzy', 'Due to their short legs and long backs, jumping puts significant stress on the spine and can trigger or worsen IVDD.', 'Using ramps or pet stairs can help prevent spinal injuries.', 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'medium', 'What hereditary joint condition causes the hip socket to develop abnormally?', 'Hip dysplasia', 'Patellar luxation', 'Elbow dysplasia', 'Legg-Calve-Perthes', 'Hip dysplasia is a genetic condition where the hip joint doesn''t develop properly, leading to arthritis and pain.', NULL, 0, 1),

('health_wellness', 'hard', 'What does "tracheal hypoplasia" mean in French Bulldogs?', 'An abnormally narrow windpipe from birth', 'A collapsed trachea', 'An inflamed windpipe', 'A trachea that grows too long', 'Tracheal hypoplasia means the trachea is smaller in diameter than normal, which further restricts airflow in an already compromised brachycephalic airway.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'hard', 'What CHIC health tests does the FBDCA recommend for breeding French Bulldogs?', 'Hip, patella, eyes, cardiac, and BOAS evaluation', 'Only DNA panel testing', 'Only hip X-rays', 'Blood work and urinalysis only', 'The Canine Health Information Center (CHIC) list includes evaluations for hip dysplasia, patellar luxation, eye disease, cardiac issues, and BOAS.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'hard', 'What eye condition causes the cornea to become cloudy and is hereditary in French Bulldogs?', 'Corneal dystrophy', 'Cherry eye', 'Cataracts', 'Progressive retinal atrophy', 'Corneal dystrophy causes the outer surface of the eye to become opaque. While not usually painful, it increases susceptibility to corneal ulcers.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'hard', 'What is retinal dysplasia in French Bulldogs?', 'Abnormal formation of the retina causing vision issues', 'A swollen retina from infection', 'Detachment of the retina', 'Scarring on the retina', 'Retinal dysplasia is inherited and causes abnormal retina formation. Severe cases can cause significant vision loss or blindness, and there is no treatment.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'hard', 'Why is breeding two merle French Bulldogs together considered dangerous?', 'It can cause deafness, blindness, and other severe birth defects', 'It produces all-white puppies that are harder to sell', 'It results in puppies that are too large', 'It causes coat colour that is not AKC standard', 'Double merle (homozygous merle) puppies have a significantly higher risk of serious health problems including hearing and vision defects.', NULL, 0, 1),
('health_wellness', 'hard', 'What gastrointestinal condition can cause a Frenchie to regurgitate food due to a stomach hernia?', 'Hiatal hernia', 'Bloat (GDV)', 'Pyloric stenosis', 'Megaesophagus', 'Hiatal hernias occur when part of the stomach pushes through the diaphragm, causing regurgitation. They are more common in brachycephalic breeds.', NULL, 0, 1),

